cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the scope of cs.CL.
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with speech corpus and speech quality, which are related to sound processing and analysis. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): ASR involves signal processing techniques for feature extraction and modeling, which falls under the scope of cs.SI.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper mentions supervised learning for ASR and reports the performance of baseline models, which indicates the use of machine learning techniques.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper mentions safety issues related to collecting raw speeches from real systems, which falls under the scope of cs.CY.
